comments: Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Simmons' (PHI) path and braces himself as he absorbs the contact from Simmons.
Embiid (PHI) makes contact with the pass to Gobert (UTA) and makes incidental contact with Gobert's off-arm while the ball is loose.  The two players then briefly engage prior to the whistle.
Mitchell (UTA) commits a take foul on Simmons (PHI).
Gobert (UTA) defends the entry pass and marginal contact occurs with Embiid's (PHI) body as he receives the pass.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact to Embiid's (PHI) arm and body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Mitchell (UTA).
Gobert (UTA) makes contact with the ball after it rolls off of the rim and is outside of the imaginary cylinder above the basket ring during his putback dunk.
Conley (UTA) and Simmons (PHI) make incidental foot to foot contact as Simmons cuts to the perimeter.
Bogdanovic (UTA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Embiid (PHI) draws Gobert (UTA) into the air towards him and Gobert (UTA) makes contact to his arm that affects his post shot attempt.
Curry (PHI) makes contact to Bogdanovic's (UTA) arm in the post and the contact affects his ability to bring two hands to the ball.
Bogdanovic (UTA) slides his pivot foot while trying to avoid the defensive pressure.
During the inbound, Simmons (PHI) and Mitchell (UTA) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Simmons (PHI) jumps and extends his leg out to make contact with the ball on the pass by Bogdanovic (UTA), which causes it to go into the backcourt.
During the rebound, Gobert (UTA) and Embiid (PHI) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Mitchell (UTA) does not get any part of his hand underneath the ball as he splits the double team. Any contact to his arm is deemed marginal as it does not affect his SQBR.
Embiid (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Mitchell (UTA) and cleanly blocks the shot.
Embiid (PHI) makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm that affects his shot attempt near the basket after the blocked shot.
Mitchell (UTA) dives to the floor to pursue the loose ball and any contact with Thybulle's (PHI) foot is deemed incidental as he loses his balance.
During the rebound, Mitchell (UTA) and Thybulle (PHI) try to gather the loose ball and the ball goes off of Thybulle's planted foot.
Conley (UTA) and Harris (PHI) come together at the end of his drive and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his ability to make his intended pass.

The call on the floor is that O?Neil (UTA) deflects the ball into a referee standing out of bounds and it is 76ers possession.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor is confirmed.
Gobert (UTA) collapses his forearm to absorb the contact from Harris (PHI) and marginal contact occurs to Harris' arm that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Curry (PHI) commits a take foul on Conley (UTA).
Bogdanovic (UTA) crowds Embiid (PHI) as he receives the pass and marginal contact occurs.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Milton's (PHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Embiid (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Conley (UTA).
Any contact between Milton (PHI) and Gobert (UTA) is deemed incidental as it occurs after the game clock expires.
Mitchell (UTA) wraps his arm around Simmons' (PHI) leg during the drive and the contact restricts his movement.
Harris (PHI) does not go through O'Neale's (UTA) space at the end of his drive and the contact is marginal as he releases into his step back jump shot.
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence that confirms if O'Neale (UTA) makes contact to Harris' (PHI) arm during the jump shot attempt.
Milton (PHI) makes incidental foot to foot contact with Conley (UTA) and the contact does not affect Conley's intended pass.

Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Harris' (PHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact. The contact as the engage and disengage when Gobert starts his roll to the rim is marginal.
During the rebound, Embiid (PHI) and Gobert (UTA) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Harris (PHI) lifts and re-plants his foot during his spin move on his post shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Bogdanovic (UTA) brings his arm forward and marginal contact occurs during Harris' (PHI) shot attempt near the rim.
During the rebound, O'Neale (UTA) has a resting forearm on Simmons' (PHI) back and the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to get to the ball.
Simmons (PHI) loses control of the ball during his putback shot attempt at the basket and any contact by Gobert (UTA) to his chest while he loses control is marginal.
Gobert (UTA) extends his forearm into Embiid's (PHI) back and the contact affects his play at the basket.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Gobert (UTA) is deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Simmons (PHI) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs to Mitchell's (UTA) leg that does not affect his SQBR.
Mitchell (UTA) does not step out of bounds during his step back jump shot attempt.
Simmons (PHI) avoids making contact with Mitchell (UTA) when he contests his jump shot attempt.

Bogdanovic (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position on Milton (PHI) and Milton loses his balance as he tries to switch directions. Milton goes to the ground after the ball and Bogdanovic makes clean ball contact to tie it up for a whistled jump ball.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Conley (UTA) makes contact to Harris' (PHI) arm that affects his intended pass.
Milton (PHI) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
As Harris (PHI) secures the rebound, Bogdanovic (UTA) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs to Harris' (PHI) leg that does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball.
